I've pushed a fix in eec3cc2b0edf93e547739534869f4f4c23244e4e.

It had nothing to do with Linode API after all. The problem was that Linode driver overrides `Response.__init__` and didn't correctly handle response body when using `LoggingConnection` (`LoggingConnection` is used when `LIBCLOUD_DEBUG` environment variable is specified).

Down the road, I also want to remove duplicated logic in `LinodeResponse.__init__` and just rely on the base `Response` class which handles all the known edge cases correctly.

@JuanCarlosM Thanks anyway.

@fly Ignore my last comment :)

@Itxaka Thanks.

I'm having troubles applying this patch on top of trunk (I would squash the commits myself). Can you please sync your branch with latest trunk and squash all the commits?

In the worst case, if you are also having troubles, just sync your branch with trunk, do git diff --no-prefix trunk > t.diff, create new branch, git apply t.diff and commit all the changes under a single commit.

@baldwinSPC How are things looking for those last couple of issues?

I will probably be preparing a new release this weekend and it would be great if those things could get addressed so I can also include this driver.

If you can't do it this weekend, let me know and I will do it myself (address those issues + squash the commits) while merging the patch.

@baldwinSPC I performed another review. During the review I still spotted many issues (mostly with function claiming it returns a single object but it actually returned a list) which I have fixed in my branch - https://github.com/Kami/libcloud/commit/28e9774b601c4081d86c9ac4c6b3dd619d1470ea

I would appreciate if you can go over my fixes, double check them and test them with the actual Profitbricks API (I don't have an account).

Thanks!
